			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>WOW vs EQ2 vs EQ advice</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>My wife and I have played EQ for over 4 years. We both have 65+ toons and many alts. Obviously we very much enjoyed EQ over the years. Now we are seeing many of our friends leave EQ for EQ2 or WOW. We have also added children to our family which cuts down on the big blocks of time we used to have on the game. I am looking for some advice from EQ folks who have played EQ2 and/or WOW. Thank you in advance!<br />
<br />
1. Down time. Has this been addressed/ improved in the new games? We often play together just the two of us and often have to stop pulling, kiting, etc... just to med and regen. <br />
<br />
2. Solo/ duoability. SOE pushed the group thing upon us and gave soloist/duoists a severe disadvantage in both xping and questing. How is this in the new games? <br />
<br />
3. Time sink. Since we have had to cut down on our online time, we seem to eat up a ton of our gaming time camping, buffing, etc... Any improvements here? I have heard there are quests that are time dependant in the new games.<br />
<br />
4. Quests. We like quests, but the way EQ is now, quests we can complete almost never reward us with anything we can use/need. And to make matters worse, anything that we can use/ need is usually impossible for my wife and I to handle alone. <br />
<br />
We are not anti-social and we do group, but often we like to grab a glass of wine, log on for an hour or two and go have fun. This is becoming more and more difficult in EQ and we were wondering if any of you could set us straight on the new games we are considering. <br />
Cheers and Thanks!</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
