		<!-- message -->
		<div>My background in EQ1 was being in a raiding guild - we raided 5-6 nights a week. As you might expect from this site I played a wizard and so had somesolo options available for off nights in addition to guild groups,LDoN etc.<br />
<br />
IMO the main difference between WoW and EQ1 is that WoW seems like a game whereas EQ1 seemed more like a vocation.<br />
<br />
As a game it's much easier to pick WoW and set it down again. I'm less striken by guilt and don't feel I've wasted my time. If I have only an hour to play I still feel like I can accomplish something in WoW - it's been a long while since I felt that way about an hour in EQ1 (I guess really since I hit 1750)<br />
<br />
But it goes deeper than that - WoW seems to be structured to fascilitate just that casual play style - you get to places faster, you regen faster etc. While it might take 30 minutes to get a group setup in EQ1, it's simply not needed in WoW. Same thing wth quests - they are an integral part of character progression - sort of like EQ1 used to be.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
