	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Soldarin</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">We appreciate the info! Thanks! Im thinking about looking into WOW. sounds pretty good for what we want. After looking through the WOW boards (cant post there yet, since I am not a player or beta tester) I read about contested zones? Are these zones where pvp takes place even on blue servers? If so, that would be very cool and EQ should think about that.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
On a normal, or RP server, it's harder to need to worry about PVP. 'Contested' areas are a PVP server type thing.<br />
<br />
Basically, on normal and RP, you are only open to pvp if you meet one of a short list of qualifiers. You set yourself pvp (/pvp), you attack a factioned NPC of the opposing faction (known by their portrait), you buff/heal/assist someone on your side who is currentl set pvp (which can include buffing or healing factioned NPCs on your side), or you opt to attack an opposing player who is set pvp.<br />
There may be a couple more ways, and there are definitely ways to game the system to provoke the pvp flag being set (such as setting yourself pvp, and stealthing/standing next to an AE using caster, so they accidentally tag you while doing PVE and set themselves as a result. Or standing on top of their fishing bobber when it splashes, so you right click them instead of the bobber, which starts a fight, or mind controlling a mob you're fighting, so you attack a 'factioned' target... this last one is being fixed in tomorrow's patch).<br />
<br />
On a PVP server, each side has 'safe' areas (usually the zones directly adjacent/containing their capitals) .In a safe area, you can freely attack enemy PCs, but they can only attack you if you meet the conditions of pvp on a regular server (so /pvp, buff a factioned friendly, attack an enemy PC, etc).<br />
They also have contested areas (which are most of the areas in between 'safe' and 'hostile'), where you can freely attack (and be attacked by) enemy PCs.<br />
There are also 'hostile' areas, which is when you're in one of THEIR safe areas. You can attack factioned NPCs, but can't touch the PCs unless they set themselves pvp, attack you, heal/assist a factioned PC/NPC fighting you, etc.<br />
<br />
I play a normal and RP server, so my grasp of PVP servers may be lacking, but I'm near certain the above is accurate.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
